## Data Flow & Communication Pattern

All client-server communication follows **one consistent pattern**:

```
JS (sendAjax) ──POST JSON──▶ PHP endpoint ──mysqli──▶ MySQL
                                  │
                          JSON response
                                  │
JS callback ◀──────────────────────
```

The [sendAjax()](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/JS/loginpage.js#336-349) helper is **duplicated** in [loginpage.js](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/JS/loginpage.js) and [questionnaire.js](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/JS/questionnaire.js):

```javascript
function sendAjax(url, data, callback) {
    var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
    xhr.open("POST", url, true);
    xhr.setRequestHeader("Content-Type", "application/json");
    xhr.onreadystatechange = function() {
        if (xhr.readyState === 4) {
            callback(JSON.parse(xhr.responseText));
        }
    };
    xhr.send(JSON.stringify(data));
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> Many modules (dashboard, course, profile, admin pages) use **hardcoded mock data** or **localStorage/sessionStorage** instead of real AJAX calls. The PHP API layer currently only covers authentication and VARK style saving.

