## PHP API Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| [login.php](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/PHP/login.php) | POST | Email/password auth → session creation, returns role + learning_style |
| [signup.php](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/PHP/signup.php) | POST | Register (username + email + bcrypt password), unique checks |
| [forget_password.php](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/PHP/forget_password.php) | POST | Verify email exists, block admin password resets |
| [reset_password.php](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/PHP/reset_password.php) | POST | Reset password (validates not same as old, bcrypt hash) |
| [save_learning_style.php](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/PHP/save_learning_style.php) | POST | Save VARK result to `users.learning_style` (session-protected) |
| [connect_db.php](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/PHP/connect_db.php) | — | Shared `mysqli` connection to `edume` database |

All endpoints follow this pattern:
- Read raw `php://input` → `json_decode`
- Validate input → Prepared statements (`bind_param`)
- Return `json_encode(["status" => ..., "message" => ...])`

---

## Key Observations

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### What's Working (Connected to Backend)
> - ✅ Login / Register / Forgot Password / Reset Password
> - ✅ VARK Assessment → saves learning style to DB
> - ✅ Session-based auth with role-based redirects (student vs admin)

> [!WARNING]
> ### What's Using Mock/Local Data (Not Yet Connected)
> - ⚠️ **Dashboard** — [loadUserData()](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/JS/coding.js#454-471) uses hardcoded `John Doe` data
> - ⚠️ **Course catalog** — enrollment tracked in `localStorage` only
> - ⚠️ **Python course** — chapter data, resources, quizzes all hardcoded in JS
> - ⚠️ **Coding sandbox** — code save/load uses `localStorage`
> - ⚠️ **Profile** — all profile data in `localStorage`/`sessionStorage`
> - ⚠️ **Admin dashboard** — uses mock data with `setTimeout` simulating API calls
> - ⚠️ **Admin course management** — full CRUD but using `localStorage` JSON, not MySQL
> - ⚠️ **Admin user management** — [fetchUsersData()](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/JS/user_manage_admin.js#41-94) generates mock users
> - ⚠️ **Support center** — mock report data
> - ⚠️ **Gravatar API** — mentioned as a requirement but not yet integrated anywhere

> [!NOTE]
> ### Architecture Patterns
> - **No shared JS module** — [sendAjax()](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/JS/loginpage.js#336-349) is duplicated, [showNotification()](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/JS/dashboard.js#175-201) has different implementations per file
> - **No session validation middleware** — only [save_learning_style.php](file:///d:/School/CapstoneProject/Edume/PHP/save_learning_style.php) checks `$_SESSION`; other pages don't verify auth
> - **No CORS or CSRF protection** on PHP endpoints
> - **Database schema is more mature than the code** — the 14-table schema supports features (progress tracking, achievements, quiz attempts, VARK questions from DB) that the frontend doesn't use yet
